  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.ItemSelectable, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.MenuElement, javax.swing.SwingConstants, FrameAccessorInterface
    public class BaseRadioButtonMenuItem
extends javax.swing.JRadioButtonMenuItem
implements FrameAccessorInterface
    This class creates a base radio button menu item. ActionListener, mnemonic, keyboard shortcut, and title are set via the constructor.

    A BaseInternalFrame object may optionally be associated with an instance of this class.
    Version:
    1.0 11-Aug-2001

      • BaseRadioButtonMenuItem

        public BaseRadioButtonMenuItem​(java.awt.event.ActionListener listener,
                               java.lang.String itemTitle,
                               int mnemonic,
                               int shortcut,
                               boolean selected,
                               BaseInternalFrame associatedFrame)
        creates the BaseRadioButtonMenuItem with an associated frame. Used for radio menu items that are associated with an internal frame.
        Parameters:
        listener - the action listener to assign
        itemTitle - the title of the item
        mnemonic - the mnemonic used to access the menu
        shortcut - the keyboard shortcut used to access the menu. -1 indicates no shortcut.
        selected - boolean that indicates whether the menu item is selected or not
        associatedFrame - the BaseInternalFrame associated with the menu item
